2. Using RDD and FlaMap count how many times each word appears in a file and write out a list of words whose count is strictly greater than 4 using Spark. 
 val textFile = sc.textFile("/home/bhoom/Desktop/wc.txt") 
val counts = textFile.flatMap(line => line.split(" ")).map(word => (word, 1)).reduceByKey(_ + _) import scala.collection.immutable.ListMap 
val sorted=ListMap(counts.collect.sortWith(_._2 > _._2):_*)// sort in descending order based  on values 
println(sorted) 
for((k,v)<-sorted) 
{ 
if(v>4) 
{ 
print(k+",") 
print(v) 
println() 
} 
} 
